</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E2738160C9C88BAFEE335C30" blockId="5.[174,1233,1293,1861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="502">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be readily distinguished from other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE2738160C9858B8EEB4D5C70" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[174,297,1514,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE2738160C9858B8EEB4D5C70" box="[174,297,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="502">Geloemyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: 1 or, face with epistome 0.3× as high as antennal grooves, the latter entirely fused, vein R 
<subScript id="AC1E349CE2738160CA168879E93C5C5F" attach="left" box="[829,856,1565,1579]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="502">4+5</subScript>
setulose, female fore tarsus with tarsomeres 4 and 5 widened in female; mid femur with femoral organ in female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E2738160C9C8882FE8235CD1" blockId="5.[174,1233,1293,1861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="502">
D e s c r i p t i o n (partly modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E2738160CB9A882EE9165C11" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[689,882,1610,1637]" pageId="5" pageNumber="502" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Body brownish yellow, with reddish yellow to reddish-brown pattern; setae and setulae black; mesonotum length 
<quantity id="F7629B3CE2738160CDBB880EEB735CD1" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.55" metricValueMin="1.95" pageId="5" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.55" valueMin="1.95">1.95– 2.55 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="F7629B3CE2738160C89F88EEE8275CD1" box="[436,579,1674,1701]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" metricValueMax="7.6" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="6.6" valueMax="7.6" valueMin="5.6">5.6–7.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E2738163C9C888CEEEAD5F97" blockId="5.[174,1233,1293,1861]" lastBlockId="6.[166,1225,1160,1859]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="503" pageId="5" pageNumber="502">Head (fig. 26) reddish yellow, length: height: width ratio = 1: 1.2: 1.3; frons reddish yellow to reddish brown with sparse fine setulae, anteriormost setulae half as long as orbital setae; frons 1.4× as long as wide, 0.36–0.45× as wide as head, gena 0.55–0.63× as high as eye in male and 0.36–0.52× in female; medial vertical seta 1.1–1.4× as long as horizontal diameter of eye; outer vertical seta 0.55–0.65× as long as medial vertical seta in male, 0.47–0.51× in female; postocellar seta 0.37–0.51× as long as medial vertical seta; ocellar seta 0.23–0.43× as long as medial vertical seta; 1 orbital seta: frontal setae absent; antenna yellow to reddish yellow; flagellomere 1 oval, brownish yellow to reddish yellow microtrichose, apically rounded, 1.5× as long as wide, 0.86–1.0× as long as pedicel; first flagellomere; arista short pubescent; eye elliptic 0.63–0.70× as long as high; face pale yellow to reddish yellow; antennal grooves deeply concave, without median carina, 0.74–0.84× as high as face; epistome low, 0.15–0.25× as high as face; gena and postgena reddish yellow; occiput reddish yellow to brownish yellow with short supracervical setae, 1 long postocular seta; all setulae at anterior margin of postgena subequal; mouthparts pale yellow, labellum with yellowish brown setulae, prementum yellow with 2 moderately short setae at each side; palp yellow to reddish yellow, wide and moderately long, 2× as long as wide and almost as wide as flagellomere 1.</paragraph>
<caption id="64E56651E2708163C99B8A5EE99D5E1F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452707" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452707" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452707/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="503" startId="6.[176,209,1082,1104]" targetBox="[196,1164,183,1067]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="302536D9E2708163C99B8A5EE99D5E1F" blockId="6.[176,1222,1081,1131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="503">
Fig. 23–28. 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE2708163C80B8A5EEBD85E3B" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="Kim, Han &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[288,444,1082,1103]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE2708163C80B8A5EEBD85E3B" box="[288,444,1082,1103]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="503">Geloemyia cheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="19DD57B0E2708163C8E38A5EEB985E24" box="[456,508,1082,1104]" pageId="6" pageNumber="503" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype ♀ (SIZK): 23 — habitus, lateral view; 24 — mid femur and tibia, anterior view; 25–26 — head (25 — anterior, 26 — lateral view); 27 — wing; 28 — label.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="302536D9E2708163C9F08B8DE8935D37" blockId="6.[166,1225,1160,1859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="503">
Thorax (fig. 21, 31, 32) reddish yellow to brownish yellow with brown to reddishbrown pattern; postpronotal lobe pale yellow to brownish yellow with 1 seta and 4–8 setulae; scutum with 1 presutural supra-alar, 1 scapular seta (scap), 3 postsutural dc, and 1 prst ac seta, and also 1 postsutural supra-alar, 1 intra-alar, 1 postalar and 2 notopleural setae; round dark brown spot ventral of postsutural supra-alar seta; mesonotum with brown or reddish brown lyrate pattern at incertions of dorso-ventral muscles; scutellum pale yellow to brownish yellow, bare; apical scutellar seta 1.8–2.9×, basal scutellar seta 1.6–2.5× as long as scutellum; pleura (fig. 23, 32; 
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E2708163CB0D88ADE8825C97" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[550,742,1737,1763]" pageId="6" pageNumber="503" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE2708163CBD988ADE93C5C97" box="[754,856,1736,1763]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="503">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
) pale yellow to reddish yellow; proepisternum with 2–7 setae; 1 anepisternal seta and 2–4 long setulae and relatively short setulae in posterior part of anepisternum; 1 katepisternal, 1 anepimeral seta; katepimeron pale yellow to reddish yellow; mediotergite brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E2718162C9C88ED4EE335B9D" blockId="7.[174,1233,175,586]" pageId="7" pageNumber="504">
Legs (fig. 23, 24) pale yellow to brownish yellow; fore coxa as on fig. 33; fore trochanter unmodified, with 3 fine setulae; fore femur brownish yellow with erect setulae, posterodorsally with 3 dorsal setae, postero-ventrally with 4–6 setae shorter than postero-dorsal ones; female fore tarsus modified: tarsomeres 
<quantity id="F7629B3CE2718162CBFE8F6BE9465B5D" box="[725,802,271,298]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" metricValueMax="1.27" metricValueMin="0.762" pageId="7" pageNumber="504" unit="in" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 in</quantity>
female modified: tarsomere 3 wide, 1.5× as wide as tarsomere 2; tarsomere 4 enlarged and asymmetrical, anterior half flattened, short and sparsely setulose on dorsal surface, tarsomere 5 smaller than tarsomere 4, with 6–7 long setulae on anterior margin longer than claws; male fore tarsus unmodified; mid coxa and trochanter unmodified, as on fig. 34; mid femur with short dense setulae, anterodorsally in medial part with large oval femoral organ, almost half as long as femur, and not concave; hind femur with 2–5 apicodorsal setae and long antero-ventral setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E271816DC9C88F8BEBE45B7E" blockId="7.[174,1233,175,586]" lastBlockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="505" pageId="7" pageNumber="504">
Wing of female hyaline with extensive brown banded pattern (fig. 27; 
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E2718162CD3B8F8BEEA8587D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[1040,1228,495,522]" pageId="7" pageNumber="504" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE2718162C9858C6BEB70585E" box="[174,276,527,554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="504">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
); wing bands broader and darker in males; humeral break present, subcostal break almost inconspicuous; Sc incomplete at C; cells bm and cu 
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE2718162CA528C54E9E3583D" box="[889,903,560,585]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="504">p</emphasis>
covered with microtrichia; vein R 
<subScript id="AC1E349CE27E816DC9D98EA6EB695AA4" attach="left" box="[242,269,194,208]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">4+5</subScript>
setulose dorsally; halter yellow. Wing of male with wide crossbands, similarly to those in 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE27E816DC8218EB4EBA65A9D" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[266,450,207,234]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Parageloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofasciata">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE27E816DC8218EB4EBA65A9D" box="[266,450,207,234]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">G. nigrofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="EF21887BE27E816DC8E38EABE84B5A9D" box="[456,559,207,233]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">holotype</typeStatus>
(as on fig. 73), but differing in subapical crossband often broken on vein M.
</paragraph>
<caption id="64E56651E2718162C99B88B4EBC35D42" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452711" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452711/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="504" startId="7.[176,209,1744,1766]" targetBox="[219,1191,624,1714]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="302536D9E2718162C99B88B4EBC35D42" blockId="7.[176,1235,1743,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 29–37. 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE2718162C83588B4EBDD5C91" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="Kim, Han &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[286,441,1744,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE2718162C83588B4EBDD5C91" box="[286,441,1744,1765]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="504">Geloemyia cheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="19DD57B0E2718162C8EF88B4EB9C5C92" box="[452,504,1744,1766]" pageId="7" pageNumber="504" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype ♀ (MHNG): 29 — head, dorsal view; 30 — occiput, posterior view; 31–32 — thorax (31 — dorsal, 32 — lateral view); 33 — fore coxa, anterior view; 34 — mid coxa, anterior view; 35–36 — abdomen (35 — dorsal, 36 — lateral view); 37 — apex of oviscape, ventral view. Drawings by the author, incl. pencil drafts.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="302536D9E27E816DC9F08F6BE9255B1D" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">
Male abdomen (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DC88E8F6BE80A5B5D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[421,622,271,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DCB558F6BE9775B5E" box="[638,787,271,298]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Figs 14C, D</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown, densely setulose, laterally long setulose; syntergite 1+2 1.8× as long as tergites 3–4 combined; tergite 5 0.64– 0.7× as long as syntergite 1+2; sternites 3–4 subquadrate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E27E816DC9F08F0BE93F5BBD" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Female abdomen (figs 35–37) reddish yellow to brownish yellow; syntergite 1+2 1.54– 2.35× as long as tergites 3–6 combined; tergites 5–6 short, sometimes hidden in dorsal view; sternites 1+2 and 6 trapezoid, sternites 3–5 subrectangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E27E816DC9F08FABEB13585D" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">
Male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DC8B78FABE8025B9D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[412,614,463,490]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DCB5C8FABE8AB5B9E" box="[631,719,463,490]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Figs 15</figureCitation>
E-H): epandrium dorsally bare, with few laterodorsal setulae; cerci with relatively short sparse setulae; surstylus distinctly protruding postero-ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E27E816DC9F08C4BEB65595D" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">
Female terminalia: oviscape tapering towards apex (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DCA028C4BE986583D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[809,994,559,586]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DCAC78C4BEE29583E" box="[1004,1101,559,586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
) brownish yellow, in apical one-fifth or one-sixth dark brown, with pair of ventrolateral rows of 5–6 slightly thickened and elongated setulae, laterally and dorsally with suberect, unmodified setulae; 1.59–2× as long as preabdominal tergites combined and 1.05–1.1 times as long as thorax; apex black with 3–4 pairs fairly long and stout setae ventrally (fig. 37); aculeus barbed, with conspicuous subapical constriction (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DCBC38CABE9C1589D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[744,933,719,746]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DCA848CABEE75589E" box="[943,1041,719,746]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
); 3 smooth oval spermathecae (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DC87C8C8BE873597D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[343,535,751,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DCB098C8BE8E3597E" box="[546,647,751,778]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
); egg (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DCBFF8C8BE9F0597D" author="Kim, S. - K. &amp; Han, H. - Y." box="[724,916,751,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="255 - 291" refId="ref13368" refString="Kim, S. - K., Han, H. - Y. 2001. A systematic study of the genera Adapsilia and Parageloemyia in Korea (Diptera, Tephritoidea, Pyrgotidae). Insecta Koreana, 18 (3), 255 - 291." type="journal article" year="2001">Kim, Han, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DCAB48C8BEE62597E" box="[927,1030,751,778]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[173,206,1089,1111]" captionTargetBox="[244,1201,177,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[224,1207,174,1078]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 11–22. Geloemyia ǫ, three apical right fore tarsomes, dorsal view (11–16) and apex of oviscape, left view (17–22): 11, 17 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 12 — G. trifasciata; 13, 18 — G. cockerelli; 14, 19 — G. stylata; 15, 20 — G. cheni, sp. n.; 16, 21 — G. quadriseta; 22 — G. wonjuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
) oblanceolate in outline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E27E816DC9F08D4BE850593D" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" box="[219,564,814,842]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">
Wing length ♂: 5.8, 
<geoCoordinate id="55AE501EE27E816DC8EE8D4AE866593D" box="[453,514,814,842]" degrees="6.4" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" precision="5555" value="-6.4">♀ 6.4</geoCoordinate>
–6.8
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302536D9E27E816DC9F08D34E83E599D" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">
R e m a r k s. As was noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DCB638D2BE896591E" author="Hering, E. M." box="[584,754,847,874]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="288 - 295" refId="ref13328" refString="Hering, E. M. 1940. Acalyptraten aus Manchukuo. (Diptera: Pyrgotidae, Drosophilidae, Otitidae). Arbeiten uber morphologische und taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem, 7 (4), 288 - 295." type="journal article" year="1940">Hering (1940)</bibRefCitation>
and then by Korneyev (2004), Hendel confused the figures of 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE27E816DC8E08D14E80859FD" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[459,620,879,906]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriseta">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE27E816DC8E08D14E80859FD" box="[459,620,879,906]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">G. quadriseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE27E816DCB9B8D14E91E59FD" box="[688,890,880,906]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropunctata">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE27E816DCB9B8D14E91E59FD" box="[688,890,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">G. nigropunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
wings that was resulted in further misidentifications. A female from “Kirin: Kao-lin-tze, 
<date id="44241019E27E816DCAA58DEBEE7F59DD" box="[910,1051,911,937]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" value="1940-07-20">20.VII.1940</date>
… in Museum Heude” identified by 
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DC8B68DCBE83359BE" author="Chen, S. H." box="[413,599,943,970]" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="47 - 74" refId="ref13095" refString="Chen, S. H. 1947. Chinese and Japanese Pyrgotidae. Sinensia, 17, 47 - 74." type="journal article" year="1947">Chen (1947: 55)</bibRefCitation>
as “ 
<taxonomicName id="F79A4D5AE27E816DCBAE8DCBE9A859BD" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[645,972,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Parageloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofasciata">
<emphasis id="02EEEACBE27E816DCBAE8DCBE9A859BD" box="[645,972,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Parageloemyia nigrofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” and depicted (
<bibRefCitation id="540B4B28E27E816DCDAB8DCBEA85599D" author="Chen, S. H." pageId="8" pageNumber="505" pagination="47 - 74" refId="ref13095" refString="Chen, S. H. 1947. Chinese and Japanese Pyrgotidae. Sinensia, 17, 47 - 74." type="journal article" year="1947">Chen, 1947</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="A8A12A5CE27E816DC9C78DABEB38599E" box="[236,348,975,1002]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[169,202,1366,1388]" captionTargetBox="[204,1187,210,1339]" captionTargetId="figure-117@4.[204,1187,174,1353]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig.1–10. Geloemyia wings: 1 — G. namibica Korneyev, sp. n.; 2 — G. wonjuensis; 3–4 — G. trifasciata (3 — ǫ, 4 — Ơ); 5 — G. cockerelli; 6 — G. trifasciata holotype ǫ; 7 — G. cheni Kim, Han &amp; Korneyev, sp. n. paratype ǫ; 8–9 — G. quadriseta (8 — syntype ǫ G. quadriseta, syntype ǫ G. ornata); 10 — G. nigrofasciata holotype ǫ; dm — discomedial cel; cua — anterior cubital cell; dm-cu — discal mediocubital crossvein; cua — anterior cubital cell; arrows indicate spurious vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452701/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="505">Figs 8, 10</figureCitation>
) clearly belongs here.
</paragraph>
